===''Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2''=== {{Infobox album | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Albums --> | Name = Red Alert 2 Original Soundtrack | Type = [[Album]] | Artist = [[Frank Klepacki]] | Cover = | Cover size = 200 | Released = 2001 | Recorded = | Genre = [[Video game music|Video game soundtrack]] | Length = 63:19<ref name="Red Alert 2 track listing">{{cite web|url=http://www.emusic.com/album/Frank-Klepacki-Command-and-Conquer-Red-Alert-2-Soundtrack-MP3-Download/10890979.html|title=Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2 Soundtrack|publisher=eMusic.com|date=2008-11-19}}</ref> | Label = [[Westwood Studios]] | Producer = Frank Klepacki | Last album = | This album = | Next album = }} {{Listen|filename=01 - hell march 2.ogg|title=Hell March 2|description=Short clip of "Hell March 2" â 173 KB|format=[[Ogg]]}}
''Red Alert 2 Original Soundtrack'' is a soundtrack album containing musical tracks from the video game ''[[Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2]]'', composed by [[Frank Klepacki]] and produced by [[Westwood Studios|Westwood]]. It was originally released in 2001. The soundtrack spans 16 tracks and has a duration of approximately 63:00.
The title track of the album is a rewritten version of the original ''Hell March'' from ''[[Command & Conquer: Red Alert]]''.
Klepacki defined ''Red Alert 2''{{'}}s style with heavy metal guitar and fast-paced beats.<ref name="ra2review">{{cite web | title=Review of Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2 | author=The Logbook staff | url=http://www.thelogbook.com/pixel/command-conquer-red-alert/ | work=[http://www.thelogbook.com/ The Logbook]| accessdate=28 July 2006}}</ref> Klepacki scored the game with a [[Korg]] Tr-rack, [[Novation]] Nova Desktop, and [[Roland Corporation|Roland]] 5080.<ref name="westwoodnetinterview">{{cite web | year=2001 | title=Frank Klepacki Interview (Yuri's Revenge) | url=http://www.westwoodi.net/read.php?Articles/Frank_Klepacki_Interview | work=[http://www.westwoodi.net/ Westwood Infiltration]| accessdate=28 August 2006}}</ref>
The return to high-energy songs was owed in part to fan criticism of ''Tiberian Sun''.<ref name="avaultinterview">{{cite web | date=2006-09-17 | title=Good to the Last Note | author=Josh Horowitz | url=http://www.avault.com/articles/getarticle.asp?name=lastnote&page=4 | work=[http://www.avault.com/ Adrenaline Vault]| accessdate=27 July 2006 | archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20041106032042/http://www.avault.com/articles/getarticle.asp?name=lastnote&page=4 | archivedate=6 November 2004}}</ref> Klepacki maintained the energetic style in ''Red Alert 2''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s expansion pack ''Yuri's Revenge''.
