===''Command & Conquer: Red Alert 3''=== {{Infobox album | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Albums --> | Name = The Music of Command & Conquer: Red Alert 3 | Type = [[Album]] | Artist = [[Frank Klepacki]], [[James Hannigan]], [[Timothy Michael Wynn]] and [[Mikael Sandgren]] | Cover = | Cover size = 150 | Released = 2008 | Recorded = | Genre = [[Video game music|Video game soundtrack]] | Length = | Label = [[Electronic Arts|EA]] | Producer = EA | Last album = | This album = | Next album = }} Composer [[Frank Klepacki]] returned to write three tracks for the game. When interviewed regarding the matter, Klepacki indicated a strong desire to contribute more, but admitted that due to the fact that he is no longer being employed by Electronic Arts and currently works for [[Petroglyph Games]], this may be contractually impossible. At the ''RA3'' Community Summit in June 2008, Klepacki showed a video to the entire C&C community in which he stated that he had been hired to work on ''Red Alert 3'', and that he was composing Hell March 3, the most recent update of ''Red Alert''{{'}}s iconic theme.<ref name="ra3composer">{{cite web|url=http://www.ea.com/redalert/news-detail.jsp?id=13|title=Electronic Arts announces Red Alert 3 composer.|accessdate=2008-06-22}}</ref><ref name="frankklepackiinterview">{{cite web |url=http://evo-gamer.com/2008/02/15/frank-klepacki-exclusive-interview/ |title=Frank Klepachi - Exclusive Interview |date=2008-02-15 |publisher=Evo Gamer |accessdate=2008-02-27}}</ref>
In November 2008, Crispy Gamer <ref>http://www.crispygamer.com/features/2008-11-03/behind-the-music-of-command-conquer-red-alert-3.aspx</ref> reported that [[James Hannigan]] and [[Timothy Michael Wynn]] wrote the bulk of the game's remaining 114 minutes of music, with Hannigan composing the "Soviet March" menu theme along with music for the Empire of the Rising Sun Faction, and Wynn the music of the Allies and the remaining Soviet tracks. Music4Games has also covered the game's music score.<ref name="c&cra3music-M4Gam">{{cite web|url=http://www.music4games.net/Features_Display.aspx?id=302|title=Interview with Command & Conquer: Red Alert 3 Music Team|date=October 1, 2008|publisher=Music 4 Games|accessdate=2008-10-06}}</ref>
The band [[From First to Last]] composed several remix versions of Hell March and Hell March 2, also featured on the Red Alert 3 soundtrack shipped with the Premier Edition.<ref name="soundtrackign">{{cite web|url=http://uk.pc.ign.com/objects/142/14275460.html|title=Command & Conquer: Red Alert 3 (Premier Edition).|accessdate=2008-11-08}}</ref> The expansion pack, Uprising, scored mostly by Timothy Michael Wynn<ref>http://www.timwynn.net/news-popup.html</ref>, introduced a new track called Yuriko's Theme, it features two singers: Miriam Stockley and Satomi Morimoto. This theme was later remixed by [[Menno de Jong]] into a trance version, and it was later played at many great Trance festivals.<ref>http://forums.commandandconquer.com/jforum/posts/list/23703.page#395382</ref>
Tracks that were missing from the OST were released unofficially here, [http://forums.commandandconquer.com/jforum/posts/list/3370.page]
