==Reception and Legacy==
Before the release of [[Command & Conquer (video game)|''Command & Conquer'']], the majority of video games used [[MIDI]] files and other similar formats for music as a way to save space. Westwood was one of the first major developers to include actual audio files in their games. Although these recordings were generally of low quality compared to modern [[mp3]]s many credit Westwood for helping to popularize the concept.<ref name = "The music of C&C">{{cite web|url=http://commandandconquer.filefront.com/info/article_musicofcnc|title=The music of C&C|date=April 19, 2004|publisher=FileFront.com|accessdate=2009-08-07}}</ref>
